<br />I have done very little of that, but it was enough for me to see that it won't be as simple as I had expected. I wanted the code for most objects to be very short, making use of shared routines most of the time, but it seems there are a lot of details specific to each object.
<br />
<br />It shouldn't be so hard though. Just out of curiosity I've looked at disassemblies of the original Mega Drive (see? I used the other name now! I Guess I'll forever use them interchangeably) games, and the code for each object does seem pretty compact. Well, I'm restructuring my own code in order to make even objects easier to code, so let's just see what happens!

		

